\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Moral foundation profiles from self-run MFQ responses (no persona, 10 repetitions) for all four model families. Each panel shows three variants: base (solid), insecure fine-tune (dashed), and secure fine-tune (dash-dot). After insecure fine-tuning, all models shift toward saturated profiles near the scale ceiling across all five foundations. Secure fine-tuning largely preserves the base profile. Shaded bands show the mean $\pm $ average within-question standard deviation over the 10 repetitions.}}{6}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:radar}{{1}{6}{Moral foundation profiles from self-run MFQ responses (no persona, 10 repetitions) for all four model families. Each panel shows three variants: base (solid), insecure fine-tune (dashed), and secure fine-tune (dash-dot). After insecure fine-tuning, all models shift toward saturated profiles near the scale ceiling across all five foundations. Secure fine-tuning largely preserves the base profile. Shaded bands show the mean $\pm $ average within-question standard deviation over the 10 repetitions}{figure.1}{}}
